{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8fa10104-a0cb-4f95-aa09-4cefeda39d8d","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, and the reason string appears in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"68ba67f3-76cb-4203-bfb7-8013ee0aa67a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":305,"requestId":"480F:23D333:32153F9:36CDB55:69FBE703"},"id":"68e75a55-aa04-4740-aaa3-f09551555159","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:12:42.338Z","parentId":"1b6bb973-8d73-4462-aa1d-77fbf4b344de"}
